50|$|Galeopsis ladanum var. angustifolia or the <b>Red</b> <b>Hemp-nettle</b> is a European annual plant {{growing to}} 30cm tall. It flowers between June and October on waste ground, railway tracks, and other stony places. It is {{classified}} as critically endangered, having declined dramatically in the last 60 years due to increased fertiliser and herbicide. Modern farming techniques such as autumn cultivation have also affected the plant because they are killed before they have set seed.|$|E

